A BARMAN who sexually abusing two young girls and a teenage boy has been jailed.Aron Elvis Presley Miller, 36, of Kennishead Avenue, Glasgow, was convicted of three charges of sexual abuse committed at addressed n Drumchapel, Glasgow, between 2002 and 2013.Temporary judge John Morris QC told Miller: &quot;The jury convicted you of serious sexual offences. These matters require a substantial prison sentence.&quot;Miller was also placed on the sex offenders' register.He abused his first victim over a five- year period when she was aged between eight and 13.Miller sexually abused his second victim for four years when she was aged between eight and 12 and his third victim a 14-year-old boy on one occasion.Solicitor advocate Jim Wallace, defending, told the court that Miller continues to maintain his innocence.